  "ciliary_role": "Component of ciliary outer dynein arms and is required in cilia motility and ODA stability. In individuals with pathogenic variants in D H11, D H9 can reside in the place of D H11. Mutations confer a loss of ODAs in the distal portion of the ciliary axoneme and affects the ciliary beat pattern (30471717). Essential in distal axonemal assembly and docking of ODAs type 2, which occurs via direct interaction of D H9 with the docking complex protein CCDC114 (30471718)",
